description:
I am using ajc 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have something to do with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the issue:
1. Create a class in a subpackage such as:
   package subpackage;
   public class Test {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           System.out.println("Hello");
       }
   }
2. Compile the class using the following command:
   ajc -d subpackage subpackage\Test.java

Observed Behavior:
A directory "subpackage" is created under the existing "subpackage" directory when compiling with ajc.

Expected Behavior:
The same behavior as javac, where the compiled class is placed in the correct subpackage directory without creating an additional directory.

Steps to Reproduce:
Use the -d option while correctly compiling classes from a subpackage.
